LAGOS  – Monetary incentives have continued to come the way of Super Eagles as Bamidele Onalaja, the Group Managing Director of Revolution Plus, a renowned property develop­ment company, has promised the Nigerian national team N1 million per goal from the knockout stage of the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations in Cam­eroon. Onalaja, in a video call with Ahmed Musa, the team’s cap­tain, also said each member of the team (players and of­ficials) will get a plot of land each in any location of their choice (Lagos, Abuja, Abeo­kuta, Port Harcourt, Ibadan) if they eventually win the title. He has equally redeemed the N1million per goal pledge he made during the 2022 World Cup qualification 2nd round matches against Liberia and Cape Verde where the Super Eagles scored 4 goals in both matches. Captain, Ahmed Musa has confirmed the re­ceipt of N4 million. “I just want to make you guys happy. The one I promised during the World Cup qualifi­er I have redeemed. Also, let me say, for all goals you guys score at this knockout stage of the AFCON, Revolution Plus properties will pay you guys a million per goal. Engage Youths In Sporting Activities As Antidote To Insecurity,… Qatar: Don’t Judge Ghana By AFCON Form, Shorunmu Warns S’Eagles… “Also if you guys lift the AF­CON, every player and coaches will have a plot of Land each either in Lagos, Abuja, Port Harcourt, Ibadan, Abeokuta or anywhere of your choice. “We are Revolution Prop­erties are so excited about you and we are praying for you,” Onalaja enthused.